thread.title: Prep Softball: Iberia lands five, Vienna and Dixon four on All-District Team
thread.title_full: Prep Softball: Iberia lands five, Vienna and Dixon four on All-District Team

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Softball: Iberia lands five, Vienna and Dixon four on All-District Team
text:
The Class 2 District 5 Team was announced Thursday. 
Iberia led the way with five first-team selections, while Vienna and Dixon had four. 
Iberia’s Jordan Lawson, Faith Duncan, MacKenzie Limbach, Makayla Hall and Cailin Edwards were first-team honorees. 
Vienna’s Jordyn Steffen, Maddie Stricklan, Annie John and Bailey Wilkinson landed on the first team. 
Dixon’s Tressa Hughes, Maci Marshall, Hailey Akers and Kali Nelson made it on the first-team. 
The first team included: Cuba’s Kaitlin Edgar and Kylee McDonald, Steelville’s Reese Weber. 
The Second team: Vienna’s Megan Weiberg and Courtney Flater, Cuba’s Tiffany Gruver and Kristan England, Dixon’s Jordyn Vrba and Steelville’s MyKenzie Livesay. 
Honorable mention: Iberia’s Laney Rollins, Haley Graves, Reagan Stiebel, Emily DeVore, Dixon’s Ariel Prater, Ravin Kelley, Megan Gilbert, Sidney Campbell, Bourbon’s Alyssa Lackey and Callie Shelton and Cuba’s Hannah Mitchell. ﻿
